The cier package is released under the MIT licence (see the LICENSE and
LICENSE.md files), which covers all original package code.

The package additionally BUNDLES one third-party dataset, used as the example
dataset for the help-page examples and the getting-started vignette, under a
different licence:

  data/bfi_careless.rda
    Copyright (c) 2020 Florian Brühlmann, Serge Petralito, Lena F. Aeschbach,
    and Klaus Opwis.
    Licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International licence
    (CC BY 4.0; https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).
    Source: Brühlmann, F., Petralito, S., Aeschbach, L. F., & Opwis, K. (2020),
    "The quality of data collected online: An investigation of careless
    responding in a crowdsourced sample", Methods in Psychology, 2, 100022,
    https://doi.org/10.1016/j.metip.2020.100022 ;
    data component: https://osf.io/9vjur/ .
    Changes: only the 44 BFI-44 items and two attention-check indicators were
    retained, and the data was saved as a lazy-loaded R data object; no
    response, validity-indicator, or timing value was altered. See
    data-raw/bruhlmann-2020-data-quality-SOURCE.md for the full provenance.
